import React, { useState, useEffect } from "react"; import axios from "axios"; function Statas() { const [usersCount, setUsersCount] = useState(0); const [ordersCount, setOrdersCount] = useState(null); const [productsCount, setProductsCount] = useState(null); async function getUserCount (){ try { const response = await axios.get("http://localhost:5002/users"); setUsersCount(response.data.users.length); } catch (error) {} } useEffect(() =>{ getUserCount() }, []) useEffect(() => { // Fetch the number of users // Fetch the number of orders axios .get("your_orders_api_endpoint") .then((response) => setOrdersCount(response.data)) .catch((error) => console.error("Error fetching orders count:", error)); // Fetch the number of available products axios .get("your_products_api_endpoint") .then((response) => setProductsCount(response.data)) .catch((error) => console.error("Error fetching products count:", error)); }, []); // The empty dependency array ensures that this effect runs once when the component mounts return (
{/* Display the number of users */}

{usersCount !== null ? usersCount : "Loading..."}

Users
{/* Display the number of orders */}

{ordersCount !== null ? ordersCount : "Loading..."}

Total Orders
{/* Display the number of available products */}

{productsCount !== null ? productsCount : "Loading..."}

Available Products
); } export default Statas;
